                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Guzman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Cablegram.—Translation.—Handed to Mr. Gresham by Mr.
                        Guzman November 24.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British Minister Gosling has telegraphed to Limon orders for an English
                    man-of-war to go to Bluefields. Bequest American Government to send also a
                    cruiser to that port. Very urgent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baca.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
